OL,3,CResidents call for long term solution
OL,4,Cto ferry issues
OL,6,FDespite criticism from some ferry
OL,7,Fusers, the council says the vessel ran
OL,8,Fon 87 per cent of scheduled services
OL,9,Fin 2024.
OL,11,FStephen Hoyle, who picks up his
OL,12,Fgranddaughter from school, uses the
OL,13,Fservice up to three times a week. He
OL,14,Fsays if the ferry is not running, it
OL,15,Fcreates a 40 minute diversion.
OL,17,FHe said: "I would say a quarter of the
OL,18,Ftimes I've turned up for the ferry and
OL,19,Fit hasn't been running. For people in
OL,20,Fthis area, it's a lifeline.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/7
