OL,3,CResidents call for long term solution
OL,4,Cto ferry issues
OL,6,FWestmorland and Furness Council says
OL,7,Ftheir information system is correct.
OL,8,FIn 2021, a study concluded that an all-
OL,9,Felectric ferry was the answer - but
OL,10,Fthe project would have totalled #7m -
OL,11,Fwhich costs significantly more than
OL,12,Fthe service earns.
OL,14,FCllr Peter Thornton from Westmorland
OL,15,Fand Furness Council said: "In the long
OL,16,Fterm we'll probably end up with an
OL,17,Felectric ferry. The question is when?
OL,18,FPeople have this impression that a new
OL,19,Fferry would solve all the reliability
OL,20,Fissues. New ferries have teething
OL,21,Fproblems.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/7
